TECHHAVEN PAYMENT BACKEND - ADDITIONAL TERMS

1. SECURITY & COMPLIANCE
   This software is designed to handle payment transactions and sensitive customer
   data. When deploying this software in production, you must ensure compliance with:
   - PCI-DSS (Payment Card Industry Data Security Standard)
   - OWASP security guidelines
   - GDPR regulations (if handling EU customer data)
   - Local data protection laws

2. PAYMENT GATEWAY INTEGRATION
   This software integrates with TechHavenPay payment gateway. Usage requires:
   - Valid TechHavenPay account and API credentials
   - Compliance with TechHavenPay's terms of service
   - SSL/TLS encryption for all payment data
   - No storage of sensitive payment card information

3. DATA PROTECTION
   Users of this software are responsible for:
   - Implementing proper data backup procedures
   - Securing database credentials
   - Monitoring access logs
   - Implementing regular security audits
   - Encrypting sensitive data in transit and at rest

4. LIABILITY DISCLAIMER
   The authors and copyright holders are not liable for:
   - Data breaches or security incidents
   - Loss or corruption of payment data
   - Regulatory fines or penalties
   - Third-party payment processing failures
   - Unauthorized access to sensitive information

5. SUPPORT & MAINTENANCE
   - No guarantee of ongoing support or maintenance
   - Security patches will be provided on best-effort basis
   - Users are responsible for keeping dependencies updated
   - Regular security audits are recommended

6. CONTRIBUTION GUIDELINES
   Contributions are welcome but must:
   - Maintain security standards
   - Include appropriate tests (>80% coverage)
   - Follow existing code style and architecture
   - Include documentation updates
   - Pass security review before merge

